In what has become something short of an odd tradition, every year, traders at one of the region’s largest markets, Gikomba, and residents of low-income areas across the city of Nairobi brace themselves for what appears to be an endless occurrence of unexplained fires. In the fourth episode of #UncensoredMtaani, join Africa Uncensored’s Elijah Kanyi in a journey through Nairobi taking a look at the infamous Nairobi fires and the confusion that is the usual response from the authorities.